  Adherent MPEG analyzer (Sencore)
    To record a stream:
      Use the MPEG-2 Monitor/Recoder
      Go to Settings: Change interface and make sure the right card and
                      interface type are selected.
      Make sure Settings: Mode is trigger in order to save data to disk.
      If capturing to a new file, go to File: Create File and set up the file
      size and packet size.
      Go File: set output to select which file to store capture stream using
      Click Start button to start recording.

    To do buffer analysis:
      Use Buffer Analyser program.
      Go File: New to select the bitstream.  Specify the output report filename.
      In the Stream List window, select the PID you want to analyze
      Click the process button.

    To use VNC to view the PC connected to Sencore:
      Host name: ad953:23
      Password: sencore

  Need to manually select front port (Copper vs Fiber):
      Go to Jacobs.  Point browser to Ineoquest's IP address.
      Select System config: Front ports.


